headline.main: Oil Whipsaws as Production Seen Rising, More OPEC Cuts Discussed
headline.print_headline: Oil Whipsaws as Production Seen Rising, More OPEC Cuts Discussed

lead_paragraph: Oil prices whipsawed Monday, turning negative after the International Energy Agency forecast potential shale oil growth and waning European refined product demand, which bodes poorly for global efforts to remove a glut.
